import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Data Cleaning and Preprocessing

data['Hour'] = data['Dep_Time'].dt.hour  # Extract hour component from Departure_Time

# Data Transformation
peak_hours = [7, 9, 17]  # Define peak hours
filtered_data = data[data['Hour'].isin(peak_hours)]
grouped_data = filtered_data.groupby('Route').size().reset_index(name='Journeys')

# Data Analysis
# Sort routes by journey count in descending order

# Visualization

plt.xlabel('Route')
plt.ylabel('Number of Journeys during Peak Hours')
plt.title('Peak Hour Route Demand')
plt.xticks(range(len(sort_grouped_data)), sort_grouped_data['Route'], rotation=90)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
